CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 10, 1953, pg. 12 reads: "The Debs' Mothers...The charmingly gowned mothers, or relatives, of the debutantes pose for Teenie Harris, following their stint as "Ladies in Waiting [sic] at the Cotillion."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of twenty-one debutant mothers wearing gowns, including four seated on sofa, posed in Syria Mosque for the 1953 Alpha Kappa Alpha cotillion
